{{Infobox historian | honorific_prefix = | name = Claus Bundgård Christensen | honorific_suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | image_size = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = 1968 | birth_place = [[Holstebro]] | other_names = | residence = Denmark | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = History | workplaces = [[Roskilde University]] | patrons = | education = | alma_mater = | thesis_title = {{lang-da|Den sorte børs-krisekriminalitet i Danmark fra besættelsen til efterkrigstid-1939-53|lit=The black market - crisis crime in Denmark from the occupation to the postwar years - 1939-1953}} | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = 2003 | doctoral_advisor = <!--(or | doctoral_advisors = )--> | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = Books on collaboration and crime in Denmark during World War II | influences = | influenced = | awards = | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = {{url|http://forskning.ruc.dk/site/en/persons/claus-bundgaard-christensen(f85d84f8-d9bb-4fc7-8fc0-fbbf360085cb).html}} | footnotes = }}
'''Claus Bundgård Christensen''' (born 1968 in [[Holstebro]]) is a Danish historian and associate professor at [[Roskilde University]] known for his books related to collaboration and crime in Denmark during and following World War II.<ref name=homepage>{{cite web|url= http://forskning.ruc.dk/site/da/persons/claus-bundgaard-christensen(f85d84f8-d9bb-4fc7-8fc0-fbbf360085cb).html |website= [[Roskilde University|ruc.dk]] |title= Claus Bundgård Christensen - Research - Roskilde University |accessdate= 2017-04-11 |language= da}}</ref>
In 1998, he and historians Niels Bo Poulsen and Peter Scharff Smith published the book ''{{lang|da|Under hagekors og [[Flag of Denmark|Dannebrog]] - danskere i [[Waffen SS]]}}'' (''Under svastika and Dannebrog - Danes in Waffen SS''), acclaimed for its non-apologist and detailed description of the Danes who volunteered for service in the Waffen SS on the [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Eastern front]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://bibliotek.kk.dk/ting/object/870970-basis%3A29015481 |website= bibliotek.kk.dk |title= Under hagekors og Dannebrog : danskere i Waffen SS - Københavns Biblioteker |accessdate= 2017-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.information.dk/1998/12/hagekors-dannebrog |website= [[Dagbladet Information|information.dk]] |title= 'Under hagekors og Dannebrog' |first= Georg |last= Metz |date= 1998-12-02 |accessdate= 2017-04-11 |language= da |trans-title= 'Under svastika and Dannebrog'}}</ref> Their 2016 book ''{{lang|da|Waffen-SS : Europas nazistiske soldater}}'' (''Waffen-SS: Europe's Nazi soldiers'') has been translated to [[Dutch language|Dutch]].<ref>{{cite book| last1= Christensen |first1= Claus Bundgård |last2= Poulsen |first2= N. B. |last3= Smith |first3= P. S. |translator-last= de Boer |translator-first= Geri |title= De Waffen-SS : het Europese leger van de nazi's |publisher= Ad. Donker |publication-place= [[Rotterdam]] |nopp=yes|pages= 798 pages |year= 2016 |isbn= 9789061007203 |oclc= 960050491 |language= nl |trans-title= Waffen-SS: Europe's Nazi soldiers }}</ref>
In addition to his World War II era publications he wrote ''{{lang|da|Danskere på Vestfronten 1914-1918}}'' (''Danes on the Western Front 1914-1918''), which also received very positive reviews and won the 'History book of the year' ({{lang|da|Årets historiske bog}}) award in 2009.<ref name=homepage/><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.litteratursiden.dk/anmeldelser/danskere-paa-vestfronten-1914-1918-af-claus-bundgaard-christensen |website= litteratursiden.dk |title= Danskere på Vestfronten 1914-1918 af Claus Bundgård Christensen |first= Frederik |last= Schøler |date= 2014-07-09 |accessdate= 2017-04-11 |language= da |trans-title= Danes on the Western Front 1914-1918 by Claus Bundgård Christensen }}</ref>
Since 2010 he has been a reviewer of non-fiction books for [[Weekendavisen]].<ref name=homepage/>
