{{Orphan|date=June 2013}}
'''Mael Isa Mac MaelColuim''' (died [[Good Friday]], 1136) was described upon his death as "chief keeper of the calendar of [[Armagh|Ard-Macha]], its chief antiquary and librarian".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ucc.ie/celt/published/T100005B/ |title=Annals of the Four Masters |publisher=Ucc.ie |date= |accessdate=2012-08-14}}</ref> By the 19th century the surname appears to have been rendered as [[McCollum]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/ancestor/surname/index.cfm?fuseaction=Go.&Surname=McCollum&UserID= |title=Irish Ancestors/ Surnames |publisher=Irishtimes.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-14}}</ref>
The [[Abbot of Armagh]] at this time was [[Niall mac Áeda meic Máel Ísu]], a member of the [[Clann Sinaig]], while the [[Archbishop of Armagh]] was [[Saint Malachy|Máel Máedóc Ua Morgair]].
