Professor '''Oron Shagrir''' is an [[Israel]]i philosopher. He is Schulman Chair of [[Philosophy]] and [[Cognitive Science]] at the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] in [[Jerusalem]], Israel.<ref name="copeland17">{{cite book| authorlink1=Jack Copeland | last1=Copeland | first1=Jack | authorlink2=Jonathan Bowen | last2=Bowen | first2=Jonathan | last3=Sprevak | first3=Mark | authorlink4=Robin Wilson (mathematician) | last4=Wilson | first4=Robin | author5=et al. | title=[[The Turing Guide]] | publisher=[[Oxford University Press]] | year=2017 | isbn=978-0198747833 | pages=478–479 | chapter=Notes on Contributors }}</ref><ref name="cv">{{cite web| url=http://oronshagrir.huji.ac.il/sites/default/files/oronshagrir/files/shagrircv.pdf | title=Oron Shagrir | work=CV | first=Oron | last=Shagrir | publisher=[[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] | location=Israel | accessdate=30 January 2018 }}</ref>
Shagrir received a [[BSc degree]] in [[Mathematics]] and [[Computer Science]] and then an [[MA degree]] in Philosophy of Science (supervised by [[Itamar Pitowsky]]) from the Hebrew University of Jerusalem. He then received a [[PhD degree]] in Philosophy and Cognitive Science from the [[University of California, San Diego]] in the [[United States]] in 1995, having been supervised by [[Patricia Churchland]].
Oron Shagrir has been the [[Rector (academia)|Vice Rector]]<ref name="jbc">{{cite web| url=https://scholars.huji.ac.il/jbc/people/oron-shagrir | title=Oron Shagrir – Vice Rector | work=The Jerusalem Brain Community (JBC) | publisher=[[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] | location=Israel | accessdate=30 January 2018 }}</ref> (2013–2017) and then [[Vice President]] (2017 onwards) for [[international affairs]] at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem.<ref name="cv" />
Shagrir's areas of research interest include the conceptual foundations of (mainly computational) cognitive and brain sciences, the history and philosophy of [[computing]] and [[computability]], and "[[supervenience]]". His publications include:
* ''Computability: [[Alan Turing|Turing]], [[Kurt Gödel|Gödel]], [[Alonzo Church|Church]], and Beyond'' (with [[Jack Copeland]] and [[Carl Posy]]), [[MIT Press]], 2013. {{ISBN|978-0262527484}}.<ref name="mit-press">{{cite web| url=https://mitpress.mit.edu/authors/oron-shagrir | title=Oron Shagrir | publisher=[[MIT Press]] | accessdate=30 January 2018 }}</ref> * A special journal issue on the history of modern computing (with Jack Copeland, Carl Posy, and Parker Bright, ''[[The Rutherford Journal]]''), 2010.
Shagrir is on the editorial boards of ''[[The Rutherford Journal]]'' and the [[Springer (publisher)|Springer]] book series ''[[Studies in Brain and Mind]]''. In 2017, Shagrir contributed to ''[[The Turing Guide]]''.<ref>{{cite book| last1=Copeland | first1=Jack | authorlink1=Jack Copeland | last2=Sprevak | first2=Mark | last3=Shagrin | first3=Oron | year=2017 | chapter=Chapter 41 – Is the whole universe a computer? | editor-last1=Copeland | editor-first1=Jack |editorlink1=Jack Copeland | editor2=et al. | title=[[The Turing Guide]] | pages=445–462 }}</ref>
